    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.24.6"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">22 Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial"><del/><add>6</add></fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE MACMILLAN COMPANY
                        
                    CABLE ADDRESS
                    PACHAMAC NEW YORK</hi>
                    
                    <hi rend="italics">Publishers</hi>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE
                    OREGON 5-4000
                    
                    SIXTY ∙ FIFTH AVENUE ∙ NEW YORK 11 N.Y.
                    
                    GEORGE P. BRETT, JR. PRESIDENT
                    
                    RICHARD M. PEARSON, VICE PRESIDENT
                    
                    RUSSELL N. CARHART, TREASURER
                    
                    BRUCE Y. BRETT, VICE PRESIDENT &amp; SECRETARY</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>May 2, 1956</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route 6</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. De Wilton has told me about your interest in acquiring the plates of your <hi rend="caps">COLLECTED POEMS</hi>. You are probably aware that it is our custom, and the established custom of the publishing industry, to offer plates back to the author at a reduced cost -- usually one-half of the cost of manufacturing.</p>
                
                <p>In the case of the <hi rend="caps">COLLECTED POEMS</hi> the Editorial Council has recommended that we offer the plates to you at one-quarter of the original cost of &#36;1256.23, or &#36;314.06.</p>
                
                <p>I shall be happy to hear further from you in this matter. Please <del>t</del><add>d</add>o not hesitate to put to me any questions you may have about it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute> 
                    <signed>Emile Capouya</signed>
                    <signed>Emile Capouya
                    Assistant to Director,
                    Trade Department</signed>
                    
                    <note>EC:jrm</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
